<h2>Golden Nugget Atlantic City? It&#8217;s Real!</h2>
<p>More good news arrives for <span style="text-decoration: underline;">Atlantic City</span> as Landry&#8217;s Inc, an international restaurant and gaming operator, has announced it will buy Trump Marina Hotel Casino for $38 million.   Landry&#8217;s will put $150 million into their new casino investment for improvements, virtually the same way they resurrected the Golden Nugget in Las Vegas on Fremont.</p>
<p>In case you weren&#8217;t aware, the new Golden Nugget in Las Vegas is amazing, the extreme makeover converted a once tired casino into a state of the art attraction.  The primary piece of the puzzle is &#8220;the Tank&#8221; an attraction featuring sharks as well as a three story water slide that wows visitors. </p>
<p>The amazing thing about this deal is that Landry&#8217;s already has a clear plan for it&#8217;s new Atlantic City acquisition.  One of unique features of the <a title="Atlantic City Golden Nugget Marina Casino" href="http://www.achotelexperts.com/casinos/golden-nugget-atlantic-city.html"><strong>Golden Nugget Atlantic City</strong></a> location will be H2O Pool and Lounge.  H2O will introduce amazing fire pits and hot tubes into a year round experience at the Jersey Shore.  Other plans include: Chart House Restaurant that will overlook the Frank S. Farley Marina, several restaurants like Vic and Anthony&#8217;s Steakhouse, Grotto Italian Restorante, Red Sushi, Lillie&#8217;s Asian &amp; Noodle Bar and many more.  The Rush Lounge  will be a very cool nightlife experience for the <strong>Golden Nugget in Atlantic City</strong>.</p>
<p>Bottom line, this is fantastic news for Atlantic City.  In addition to the Governors new Tourism District and getting <a href="http://www.achotelexperts.com/casinos/revel-casino.html" class="kblinker" title="More about Revel Casino &raquo;">Revel casinos</a> financing in place, this is more good news.  Soon we also expect to hear that the Hilton Casino has a new owner, this will also contribute to better years ahead for Atlantic City, New Jersey.</p>
