<h2>Boardwalk Empire</h2>
<p><em>Atlantic City, N.J</em></p>
<p><em>HBO Drama Series</em></p>
<p><em><strong>Sunday&#8217;s at 9:00 PM</strong></em></p>
<p><em>12 Episodes</em></p>
<p>The new HBO Series <em>Atlantic City</em> &#8221;Boardwalk Empire&#8221; will air on Sunday Nights at 9:00pm.  The much anticipated series is the brain child of &#8220;The Soprano&#8217;s&#8221; Terence Winter, an Emmy Award winning writer and  executive producer. In addition to Winters, Academy Award Winning Director Martin Scorsese, directed the pilot , Mark Wahlburg Produced an episode.  He tapped several of The Sopranos ’s directors, such as Alan Taylor, Allen Coulter, and Tim Van Patten, to create this incredible new drama series based on a true story of the 1920&#8242;s during the Prohibition years in <strong>Atlantic City, New Jersey</strong> when Alcohol became illegal, the great war was over, stocks on Wall Street were about to take off and the country was changed forever.</p>
<p>The Cast Consists of: Steve Buscemi as &#8220;Nucky Thomspon&#8221;, Michael Pitt as Jimmy Darmody, Kelly Macdonald as Margaret Schroeder, Michael Shannon as Van Alden and Dabney Coleman as Commodore Kaestner.</p>
<p><em>Boardwalk Empire</em> is an amazing tale of Nucky Thompson, the undisputed ruler of Atlantic City, who was both politician and gangster. Set in Atlantic City, NJ at the beginning of prohibition, when the sale of alcohol and liquor became illegal in the United States.   The Boss of <strong>Atlantic City, New Jersey</strong> is the towns treasurer, Enoch &#8220;Nucky&#8221; Thompson played by Steve Buscemi, a corrupt politician and backroom wheeler &amp; dealer gets involved with illegal activities like rum-running and much more.</p>
<h3>&#8220;Boardwalk Empire&#8221; &#8211; Atlantic City, New Jersey</h3>
]]></content:encoded>
